    "blueprint": "All anchors verified against live code. The `parse_go_mod` scanner function exists (line 412), `_PARSERS` in shape-detect is exactly 3 entries (466-470), the MISSING_MANIFESTS guards are at 487/683, the language-reference rung at 618, and the step-auto-scope.md anchors (266 globs, 277 filter, 280-282 emptiness gate, 288-290 invocation, 344-350 scope table, 363-368 language table) all match. Now writing the blueprint.\n\n# Implementation Blueprint — SKF #427 Phase B: Tier-2 Whole-Language Detection + Ecosystem Expansion\n\n**Status:** Verified against live code at all cited anchors (2026-06-03). `parse_go_mod` exists in `skf-scan-manifests.py:412`; shape-detect `_PARSERS` has exactly 3 entries (`466-470`); MISSING_MANIFESTS guards at `487`/`683`; language-reference rung at `618`; step-auto-scope.md anchors at `266`/`277`/`280-282`/`288-290`/`344-350`/`363-368` all confirmed. **This blueprint is executable as written.**\n\nThe synthesis: **Design 1's scanner-frozen, metadata-only acquisition spine** (zero scanner change, no new envelope schema) + **Design 3's dedicated-compiler-dir gate** + the **red-team's positive-language-identity gate and strict directory-token matching** that close every one of the 6 false-positive candidates. We do NOT add `grammar_files[]`/`tree_dirs[]` envelope fields to the scanner (Designs 2/3's blast-radius cost). The grammar/tree harvest happens inline in `step-auto-scope.md` via `git ls-files`/`ls-tree` over the depth-1 clone the workflow already holds, fed directly into two new optional shape-detect args.\n\n---\n\n## 1. THE HARDENED CONJUNCTION RULE\n\nTwo independent language-reference rungs are added **above** the existing `parser_producers or parser_deps` rung (`skf-shape-detect.py:618`), so a real grammar file or a real compiler-dir triad outranks an incidental sub-tool parser dep (fixes the rust-lang/rust winnow-by-accident fragility). Both rungs share a single load-bearing exclusion gate `G` and a positive language-identity gate `L`.\n\n### Inputs (new, both optional, both default empty)\n- `grammar_files: list[str]` — repo-relative paths whose basename/extension is in the **closed** `_GRAMMAR_EXTS` set.\n- `tree_paths: list[str]` — repo-relative **directory** paths (trailing `/`) and a small set of whole-basename file signals, harvested from `git ls-tree`/`git ls-files`.\n\n### New frozensets (add near `skf-shape-detect.py:79`, after `_ALL_PARSER_DEPS`)\n\n```python\n# Closed grammar-file set — declared grammars are the strongest, most\n# intentional language signal. Matched on basename OR extension, never substring.\n_GRAMMAR_EXTS = frozenset({\n    \".g4\", \".pest\", \".lalrpop\", \".y\", \".gram\", \".lark\", \".ebnf\", \".peg\", \".ungram\",\n})\n_GRAMMAR_BASENAMES = frozenset({\"grammar.js\", \"grammar.json\", \"python.gram\"})\n\n# Concrete parsers a repo CONSUMES (formatter/linter/bundler guard). If a repo's\n# OWN runtime deps contain one of these, it delegates parsing — never a\n# whole-language reference. estree/@types/estree included per webpack red-team.\n_CONSUMED_PARSERS = frozenset({\n    \"espree\", \"acorn\", \"@babel/parser\", \"babel-parser\", \"flow-parser\",\n    \"swc_ecma_parser\", \"deno_ast\", \"graphql\", \"remark-parse\", \"yaml\",\n    \"esquery\", \"estree\", \"@types/estree\", \"@webassemblyjs/ast\", \"smol-toml\",\n})\n\n# Belt-and-suspenders: tools that own a Parser-ish module but consume an\n# external parser and are NOT whole-language references (generalized from\n# prettier/eslint to bundlers + markup/DSL libs per red-team).\n_DELEGATING_TOOL_NAMES = frozenset({\n    \"prettier\", \"eslint\", \"stylelint\", \"biome\", \"rome\",\n    \"webpack\", \"rollup\", \"esbuild\", \"vite\", \"parcel\", \"terser\",\n    \"marked\", \"remark\", \"remark-parse\", \"markdown-it\", \"micromark\", \"commonmark\",\n    \"postcss\", \"css-tree\", \"less\", \"sass\", \"node-sass\",\n})\n\n# Markup/DSL/query parsers — real tokenizer+parser+AST for a NON-general-purpose\n# language (CSS/markdown/HTML/GraphQL/JSON). Suppress the tree-triad rung for these.\n_MARKUP_DSL_NAMES = frozenset({\n    \"css\", \"less\", \"scss\", \"sass\", \"html\", \"markdown\", \"graphql\",\n    \"graphql-schema\", \"json\", \"yaml\", \"toml\", \"xml\",\n})\n\n# Closed, AUDITED compiler-dir set for the tree-triad rung (gate C).\n# NEVER add bare 'src/', 'lib/', 'language/', 'lang/', 'parser/', or 'syntax/'.\n# Matched as exact directory path tails, case-sensitive for 'Parser'.\n_COMPILER_DIRS = frozenset({\n    \"compiler\", \"src/compiler\", \"cmd/compile\", \"internal/syntax\",\n})\n_COMPILER_DIRS_CASE = frozenset({\"Parser\"})  # capital-P (CPython); case-sensitive\n```\n\n### Gate G — the delegating-consumer exclusion (load-bearing; applies to BOTH rungs)\n\n`G` is TRUE (repo is EXCLUDED) when **any** of:\n1. The repo's own **runtime** deps (`all_runtime_deps`, already computed at `:530`) intersect `_CONSUMED_PARSERS`. *(prettier, eslint, webpack, deno-via-deno_ast all excluded here)*\n2. Any own package name (`own_names`, `:585`) ∈ `_DELEGATING_TOOL_NAMES`. *(belt-and-suspenders for zero-runtime-dep tools like a refactored bundler)*\n\n### Gate L — the positive language-identity gate (NEW, from postcss/marked/graphql-js red-team)\n\n`L` is TRUE (repo IS a plausible general-purpose-language reference) when **neither** of:\n1. Any own package name ∈ `_MARKUP_DSL_NAMES` ∪ `_DELEGATING_TOOL_NAMES`, **nor**\n2. *(only for the tree-triad rung)* the repo lacks any corroborating whole-language member (see gate W below).\n\n`L` blocks postcss/css-tree/marked/markdown-it/graphql-js even if they structurally satisfy a triad, because their identity is a markup/DSL parser, not a programming-language toolchain.\n\n### RUNG A — grammar-file rung (base confidence 0.85)\n\n```\nFIRE language-reference IFF:\n  (A) grammar_files is non-empty (some path's extension ∈ _GRAMMAR_EXTS\n      OR basename ∈ _GRAMMAR_BASENAMES)\n  AND (G is FALSE)                      # not a delegating consumer\n  AND (L is FALSE on its markup/DSL clause only — clause L.1)\n```\n\n- **cpython** → `Grammar/python.gram` fires; no consumed parser; identity not markup. ✓\n- **ruby** → root `parse.y` fires; **outranks** the JIT `Cargo.toml` library-API rung because Rung A is above the existing rungs. ✓ (fixes today's library-API misclassification)\n- **Depth cap:** grammar matches are harvested at `git ls-files` depth ≤ 4 (see §3) so a deep vendored `.g4` test fixture in a non-language repo is not surfaced. The closed extension set + `_DELEGATING_TOOL_NAMES`/`_MARKUP_DSL_NAMES` guard handle the residual (an ANTLR grammars-collection repo named `grammars-v4` is the documented residual FP — accepted, bounded, not in the validation set).\n\nEmit signal `grammar_file:<basename>`.\n\n### RUNG B — tree-triad rung for hand-written compilers (base confidence 0.80)\n\nFor TypeScript/rustc/golang/go, which have **no grammar file**. Fires IFF **ALL** of `(C) ∧ (D) ∧ (G is FALSE) ∧ (L is TRUE) ∧ (W)`:\n\n**(C) Dedicated compiler dir** — `tree_paths` contains a **directory** (trailing `/`, strict path-tail token match) equal to a member of `_COMPILER_DIRS` (case-insensitive tail) or `_COMPILER_DIRS_CASE` (case-sensitive, `Parser`).\n- Strict directory-token match, **never substring, never basename**: `lib/Parser.js` (file) and `lib/src/js/compiler.dart` (file) can NEVER satisfy `Parser/` or `compiler/`. *(closes webpack `lib/Parser.js`, dart-sass `compiler.dart`/`syntax.dart`)*\n- Bare `src/` is **deliberately absent** — closes marked (`src/Parser.ts` at bare root) and postcss (`lib/`).\n- `language/`/`src/language/` deliberately absent — closes graphql-js.\n\n**(D) Lexer+parser+AST triad co-located under the (C) dir** — among `tree_paths` entries that are **descendants of the matched (C) dir**, ≥2 of these three members match, with the **parser member mandatory**:\n- *lexer*: basename ∈ {`scanner.*`, `lexer.*`, `tokenizer.*`} OR a dir/file containing `rustc_lexer`. *(`tokenize.js` deliberately NOT credited — keeps postcss out even if it had a compiler dir; `*lexer*` substring NOT used)*\n- *parser* **(mandatory)**: a file basename `parser.*`/`parse.*` OR a `parse/` dir that is a **direct child** of the (C) dir, OR `rustc_parse`/`go/parser`. Hyphenated per-language adapters (`parser-graphql.js`) do NOT match (prettier). \n- *AST*: basename ∈ {`ast.*`} (literal `ast`, **never** `node.*` — closes postcss `node.js`; **never** `ast-to-doc.js` — closes prettier) OR `rustc_ast`/`go/ast` OR the `binder.*`+`checker.*` pair (TypeScript).\n\n**(W) Corroborating whole-language member** (from marked red-team — the structural, not dir-name-based, discriminator) — `tree_paths` contains ≥1 of: a codegen/IR member (`codegen.*`, `compile.*`/`compile.c`, `opcode*`, `bytecode*`, `lower*`, `emit*`, `rustc_codegen*`), OR a VM/eval member (`interpreter.*`, `vm.*`, `eval.*`, `ceval.*`), OR a type-system pair (`binder.*`+`checker.*`). Markdown/CSS libs have lexer+parser+AST but **no codegen/VM/type-checker**, so `W` excludes marked even with a synthetic `src/compiler/` dir.\n\n**(G is FALSE)** and **(L is TRUE)** as defined above.\n\n- **rust-lang/rust** → `compiler/` dir + `rustc_lexer`/`rustc_parse`/`rustc_ast` triad + `rustc_codegen_*` (W) + identity \"rust\" ∉ markup/delegating; no consumed-parser runtime dep (winnow is rust-analyzer sub-tool only). ✓ Fires on the **intentional** signal, not the accidental winnow dep.\n- **microsoft/TypeScript** → `src/compiler/` dir + `scanner.ts`+`parser.ts`+`binder.ts`/`checker.ts` triad + `binder`+`checker` (W) + identity \"typescript\". ✓ (fixes today's reference-app misclassification)\n- **golang/go** → `cmd/compile/` + `internal/syntax/` dirs + `go/scanner`+`go/parser`+`go/ast` triad + `cmd/compile` codegen (W) + identity \"go\". ✓\n\n### Confidence\nRung A base 0.85, Rung B base 0.80, both `_clamp(..., base, 0.90)`. Emit `grammar_file:<basename>` (A) and `tree_triad:<compiler_dir>:<members>` (B).\n\n### Negative-control proof table\n\n| Repo | Rung A | Rung B | Why it stays out |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| webpack | no grammar | (C) `lib/Parser.js` is a FILE → fails strict dir-token; also G (estree/acorn dep) | strict dir-token + G |\n| postcss | no grammar | (C) `lib/` ∉ set; (D) `tokenize.js`/`node.js` not credited; (L) \"postcss\" ∈ markup | three redundant gates |\n| prettier | no grammar | (C) no compiler dir; (G) @babel/parser+acorn+espree dep; name ∈ delegating | G + (C) |\n| graphql-js | no grammar | (C) `src/language/` ∉ set; (L) \"graphql\" ∈ markup/DSL | (C) + L |\n| dart-sass | no grammar | (C) `compiler.dart`/`syntax.dart` are FILES → fail strict dir-token; (L) \"sass\" ∈ markup | strict dir-token + L |\n| marked | no grammar | (C) bare `src/` ∉ set; (W) no codegen/VM; (L) \"marked\" ∈ delegating | (C) + W + L |\n\nEvery true positive fires; every negative is blocked by ≥2 independent gates.\n\n---\n\n## 2. ECOSYSTEM EXPANSION\n\n### 2a. go.mod path (downstream-only — scanner is FROZEN)\n\nThe scanner already emits `manifests[]` with `ecosystem:\"go\"` for any Go repo (`MANIFEST_ECOSYSTEMS:112`, `parse_go_mod:412`). **No change to `skf-scan-manifests.py`.** The gap is purely downstream:\n\n1. **`skf-shape-detect.py:466-470`** — add `\"go.mod\": _parse_go_mod` to `_PARSERS`. Write `_parse_go_mod(path)` modeled on the scanner's `parse_go_mod` (single-line + block `require`, strip `// indirect`). It must return the same dict shape the other `_parse_*` return (`ecosystem:\"go\"`, `name`=module path from the `module` directive, `deps`/`runtime_deps`=required modules, `has_bin`=presence of a `cmd/` path segment in the supplied manifest path, `has_library_structure`=`bool(name)`, `export_count:0`). Add `\"go\": \"go_mod\"` to `path_to_manifest_name` (`:661`).\n2. **`step-auto-scope.md:277`** — add `go.mod` to the §2 filter whitelist: `(package.json, pyproject.toml, Cargo.toml, go.mod)`.\n3. **`step-auto-scope.md:266`** — append `'**/go.mod'` to the sparse-checkout glob list.\n4. **`step-auto-scope.md:363-368`** — add a Go row to the §5 language table: `go.mod → Go`, default include `['**/*.go']`, exclude `['**/*_test.go']`. Add `go.mod → Go` to the §5 primary-language bullets (`:356-360`). **§4 scope.type table (`:344-350`) needs NO new row** — Go libraries classify as `library-API` (→ full-library/public-api) via `has_library_structure`; whole-language Go (golang/go) is caught by Rung B, which already maps to full-library.\n\n> **LOCKSTEP TRAP (critical):** steps (1) and (2) MUST ship in the **same commit**. Widening the §2 filter without the `_PARSERS` entry converts today's graceful interactive-fallback into a **hard halt** — `_parse_manifest` would `_die(\"Unsupported manifest type: go.mod\")` → exit 2 → HALT exit 3 (empirically confirmed `UNSUPPORTED_MANIFEST`).\n\nMost pure-Go libraries (cobra, gin) now classify as `library-API`.\n\n### 2b. Manifest-less C / grammar-file path (cpython, ruby)\n\ncpython has **zero supported manifests**; ruby has only a JIT `Cargo.toml`. Both route to interactive today via §2's emptiness branch (`:280-282`). The grammar-file rung is a **second, manifest-independent reachability path** slotted at three points without disturbing the manifest-first flow:\n\n- **STEP A (acquisition, `step-auto-scope.md:266`):** widen sparse-checkout to fetch grammar files (tiny text, KB): append `'**/*.g4' '**/*.pest' '**/*.lalrpop' '**/*.y' '**/*.gram' '**/*.lark' '**/*.ebnf' '**/*.peg' '**/grammar.js' '**/grammar.json' '**/*.ungram'`.\n- **STEP B (signal harvest, NEW sub-step in `step-auto-scope.md:273-279`):** after the scanner runs, probe the SAME tree (no second clone). See §3 for exact commands. Produces `<grammar_matches>` and `<tree_paths>`.\n- **STEP C (the load-bearing routing change, `step-auto-scope.md:280-282`):** change the gate from *\"IF filtered manifest list is empty → interactive\"* to:\n\n  > **IF the filtered manifest list is empty AND no grammar files were found AND no compiler-triad directory was found → interactive.** Otherwise (empty manifests BUT grammar files OR a compiler-dir present) → proceed to §3 with **empty `--manifests`** but populated `--grammar-files`/`--tree-paths`.\n\nThis forces **one** matching change in `skf-shape-detect.py`: relax **both** MISSING_MANIFESTS guards (`:486-487` in `detect()`, `:682-683` in `main()`) to fire ONLY when `manifest_paths AND grammar_files AND tree_paths` are **all** empty. With grammar_files non-empty + manifests empty, `detect()` skips the manifest-parsing loop (already guarded by `for mp in manifest_paths`), runs Rung A, returns language-reference.\n\n> This is provably **behavior-neutral on the previously-failing path**: it can only newly-ACCEPT inputs that today hard-error. The \"empty-everything still exits 2\" regression test (§4) pins this. **Zero-manifest handling is preserved** — a plain C/JS repo with no grammar and no compiler dir still routes to interactive exactly as today.\n\ncpython (`Grammar/python.gram`) and ruby (root `parse.y`) now classify language-reference → full-library. The manifest-first flow is **untouched** for every repo that HAS a manifest.\n\n---\n\n## 3. INTERFACE & ACQUISITION CHANGES\n\n### New shape-detect args (`skf-shape-detect.py:674-679`, both optional, empty default)\n\n```python\nparser.add_argument(\"--grammar-files\", default=\"\",\n    help=\"Comma-separated repo-relative grammar file paths\")\nparser.add_argument(\"--tree-paths\", default=\"\",\n    help=\"Comma-separated repo-relative directory (trailing /) and basename structural signals\")\n```\n\nSplit both like `--manifests` (`:681` pattern). Widen `detect()` signature (`:484`) to `def detect(repo_url, manifest_paths, grammar_files=None, tree_paths=None)` with `or []` normalization inside. **Every existing 2-arg caller and all current tests stay byte-identical** (no existing branch reads the new params). Document both in `step-shape-detect.md` Arguments table (`:14-21`) and the script docstring Input block (`:29-31`).\n\n### Acquisition (`step-auto-scope.md:266` + STEP-B probe) — metadata-only, gated\n\n- **Single-line edit at `:266`** appends `'**/go.mod'` + the 11 grammar globs. `--no-cone` gitignore-glob semantics make these work directly. **Cost:** go.mod + grammar files are KB text; clone stays blobless+depth-1. **No source blobs are ever fetched** (no `*.rs`/`*.go`/`*.ts`, no `**/compiler/**` subtree).\n- **The tree-triad signal is METADATA ONLY** — derived from `git ls-tree -r -d --name-only HEAD` (directory entries) + `git ls-files` (index paths), which read LOCAL objects the depth-1 blobless clone already holds. **~0 extra fetch.** This is Design 2's `ls-tree -r -d` discipline grafted onto Design 1's scanner-frozen spine.\n\nSTEP-B probe (remote; local uses depth-capped `find`/`ls`):\n```bash\n# grammar files (depth-capped via path-depth filter)\ngrammar_matches=\"$(git -C \"$tmp\" ls-files \\\n  | grep -Ei '\\.(g4|pest|lalrpop|y|gram|lark|ebnf|peg|ungram)$|/grammar\\.(js|json)$|(^|/)python\\.gram$' \\\n  | awk -F/ 'NF<=4')\"\n# compiler dirs + triad member basenames (directory listing = free metadata)\ntree_paths=\"$(git -C \"$tmp\" ls-tree -r -d --name-only HEAD | sed 's#$#/#'; \\\n              git -C \"$tmp\" ls-files | awk -F/ 'NF<=5')\"\n```\n\n### Gating — when do we pay the tree fetch?\n\n- Only **grammar/manifest globs** are ever fetched, never source. The grammar set is KB.\n- The two `git` probe commands run over already-fetched local metadata — **no network.**\n- The probe only **changes routing in the previously-interactive empty-manifest branch.** Manifest-bearing repos are unaffected beyond a KB grammar fetch and a free metadata listing.\n- **Keep `scan-project.md` (interactive entry, parallel block at `:251`) in lockstep** if it carries its own sparse-checkout (verify; the comment at `:251` asserts it shares the helper).\n\n### §3 invocation (`step-auto-scope.md:288-290`)\n```\nuv run {shapeDetectScript} --repo-url <url> --manifests <filtered_or_empty> \\\n  --grammar-files <grammar_matches> --tree-paths <tree_paths>\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. SEQUENCED COMMIT PLAN\n\nEach commit is independently testable, test-first, and adds its new test files to **`package.json`'s `test:python` enumeration** (memory: a new test file not enumerated stays dormant in CI). All commits extend the **existing** `test/test-skf-shape-detect.py` — no new scanner test file (avoids the test:python dormancy trap). **One PR per commit; wait for merge before the next** (memory: sequential PRs).\n\n**Controls every shape-detect commit must satisfy** (fixtures = faithful reconstructions of the real trees):\n- **Positives (must fire language-reference):** rust-lang/rust, microsoft/TypeScript, python/cpython, golang/go, ruby/ruby.\n- **Negatives (must stay library-API/reference-app):** webpack, postcss, prettier, graphql-js, dart-sass, marked.\n\n---\n\n### Commit 1 — Optional args + guard relaxation (pure plumbing, behavior-neutral)\n**Files:** `skf-shape-detect.py` (args `:674-679`, split `:681`, `detect()` sig `:484`, both guards `:486-487`/`:682-683`), docstring `:29-31`; `step-shape-detect.md:14-21`.\n**Change:** add `--grammar-files`/`--tree-paths` (unused this commit); relax both MISSING_MANIFESTS guards to fire only when all three inputs empty.\n**Tests (test-first):**\n- Every existing 2-arg invocation byte-identical (regression).\n- `--manifests \"\" --grammar-files \"\" --tree-paths \"\"` → still exit 2 `MISSING_MANIFESTS` (the load-bearing pin).\n- `--manifests \"\" --grammar-files \"x.gram\"` → no longer exit 2 (returns unknown for now; Rung A lands in Commit 2).\n**Controls:** all 11 repos classify exactly as today (no rung yet).\n\n### Commit 2 — Rung A (grammar-file) + gates G & L\n**Files:** `skf-shape-detect.py` — add `_GRAMMAR_EXTS`/`_GRAMMAR_BASENAMES`/`_CONSUMED_PARSERS`/`_DELEGATING_TOOL_NAMES`/`_MARKUP_DSL_NAMES` near `:79`; insert Rung A above `:618`.\n**Tests:** cpython (`python.gram` → fires), ruby (root `parse.y` → fires, **outranks** Cargo.toml library-API), + negative: a synthetic markup repo with a `.g4` test fixture under a delegating-tool name stays library-API.\n**Controls:** cpython, ruby now fire. All 6 negatives stay out (none own a grammar file; the `.g4`-fixture case blocked by G/L). rust/TS/go unchanged (no grammar) — still classified by their existing signals this commit.\n\n### Commit 3 — Rung B (tree-triad) + gates C, D, W, strict dir-token matching\n**Files:** `skf-shape-detect.py` — add `_COMPILER_DIRS`/`_COMPILER_DIRS_CASE`; insert Rung B above Rung A (compiler-triad outranks grammar where both present, harmless); strict directory-token + case-sensitive `Parser` matcher helper.\n**Tests:** rust-lang/rust (`compiler/`+rustc triad+codegen), TypeScript (`src/compiler/`+scanner/parser/binder/checker), golang/go (`cmd/compile/`+`internal/syntax/`+go/* triad). **The 6 negatives are the heart of this commit's test suite** — each with its real near-miss shape:\n- webpack `lib/Parser.js` (file, not dir) + estree dep → library-API.\n- postcss `lib/` + `tokenize.js`/`node.js` → library-API.\n- prettier dispersed `parse/` + @babel/parser → reference-app/library.\n- graphql-js `src/language/` → library-API.\n- dart-sass `compiler.dart`/`syntax.dart` files → library-API.\n- marked bare `src/Parser.ts`, no codegen → library-API; **plus** synthetic-marked-with-`src/compiler/`-dir → still library-API (proves W, not C alone, is the guard).\n**Controls:** ALL 5 positives now fire on intentional signals; ALL 6 negatives blocked by ≥2 gates.\n\n### Commit 4 — go.mod downstream wiring (lockstep)\n**Files (one commit):** `skf-shape-detect.py` `_PARSERS:466-470` + `_parse_go_mod` + `path_to_manifest_name:661`; `step-auto-scope.md` filter `:277`, glob `:266` (`'**/go.mod'`), §5 language table `:363-368` + bullets `:356-360`.\n**Tests:** go.mod fixtures — cobra/gin → library-API; go.mod handed directly no longer hard-halts; §5 produces Go include/exclude.\n**Controls:** Go libraries → library-API; golang/go (Commit 3) still fires via Rung B.\n\n### Commit 5 — Acquisition wiring + STEP-B probe + STEP-C routing\n**Files:** `step-auto-scope.md:266` (grammar globs), STEP-B sub-step (`:273-279`), STEP-C gate rewrite (`:280-282`), §3 invocation (`:288-290`); `scan-project.md:251` lockstep check; `skf-scan-manifests.py:51-66` docstring **verify-only** (go.mod already listed).\n**Tests:** doc-level — the §2 emptiness gate now reads \"empty manifests AND no grammar AND no triad\"; §3 passes the two new args.\n**Controls (end-to-end, the acceptance gate for the whole feature):** cpython/ruby/rust/TS/go reach language-reference through the full pipeline; the 6 negatives + a plain zero-signal repo still route correctly (negatives→library-API/reference-app, zero-signal→interactive).\n\n---\n\n## 5. RISKS & DEFER LIST\n\n**Risks carried:**\n1. **Residual grammar-arm FP (bounded):** a repo that *vendors* a grammar (ANTLR `grammars-v4`, a tool shipping a `.g4` test fixture) under a non-delegating name can fire Rung A. **Mitigations in place:** closed extension set, `ls-files` depth ≤ 4, `_DELEGATING_TOOL_NAMES`/`_MARKUP_DSL_NAMES`. Not in the validation set; accepted. **Defer** a `_GRAMMAR_COLLECTION_NAMES` denylist unless a real FP surfaces.\n2. **rustc §3a cohesion interaction (must-not-regress):** rust-lang/rust has `package_count >> 3`, so §3a flags a decomposition candidate and §3b runs *before* §4. A naive per-package split would shatter rustc. **The cohesion check must MERGE** (rustc is one cohesive toolchain; `compiler/rustc` is the umbrella) — this is existing §3b \"internal building blocks\" behavior; add a regression assertion that rustc-shaped input merges, not splits.\n3. **Strict directory-token matching depends on `tree_paths` carrying trailing `/` for dirs.** The STEP-B `ls-tree -r -d ... | sed 's#$#/#'` is the single source of that invariant — a malformed probe silently breaks gate C. Pin with a fixture asserting `lib/Parser.js` (no trailing slash) never satisfies `Parser/`.\n4. **Cross-platform:** the probe runs in the workflow's bash, not Python — no Windows path concern in the script. The shape-detect matcher must use `Path(...).parts` / POSIX-form comparison (memory: `Path.as_posix`, not `str`), never OS-native separators.\n\n**Defer if any sub-part proves too large:**\n- **Defer Commit 4 (go.mod) entirely** — it is orthogonal to the language-reference rungs. Go libraries stay on the interactive route (today's safe behavior) with zero regression. Ship Commits 1-3+5 (the whole-language detection) alone; go.mod is a clean follow-up.\n- **Defer Rung B (tree-triad), keep Rung A** — if the strict directory-token matcher + gate W proves fiddly, ship grammar-file detection alone (Commits 1, 2, 5-grammar-only). That alone fixes cpython and ruby (2 of 5 positives) with the **lowest** FP surface, since Rung A touches no compiler-dir heuristic. rust/TS/go stay at today's classification (rust→language-reference via winnow accident, TS→reference-app, go→interactive) — a partial but strictly-safe win.\n- **Never defer the gate relaxation regression test** (`--manifests \"\" ...` → exit 2 when all-empty). It is the proof that the only edit to load-bearing existing code remains behavior-neutral on the failing path.\n\n**Files touched (complete):** `src/shared/scripts/skf-shape-detect.py`, `src/skf-analyze-source/references/step-auto-scope.md`, `src/skf-analyze-source/references/step-shape-detect.md`, `src/skf-analyze-source/references/scan-project.md` (lockstep verify), `test/test-skf-shape-detect.py` (+ `package.json` `test:python` enumeration). **`src/shared/scripts/skf-scan-manifests.py` — verify-only, no code change.**"
